parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Warning lights or messages on the dashboard
inability to press the brake pedal
brake pedal feels stuck or locked
sudden loss of braking power
unusual noises or vibrations when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected shattering of the sunroof can cause a loud noise, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries from flying glass.
symptoms: Loud explosion or shattering sound
sunroof breaks into little pieces without any apparent cause or warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability of the navigation system to provide accurate directions or respond to user input can cause frustration, delay, and potentially lead to accidents or getting lost.
symptoms: Navigation system fails to recognize or provide directions to specific addresses
especially new developments
system disables manual input of street names
system fails to update or provide accurate maps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the pre-collision system to warn or assist the driver in avoiding accidents can lead to collisions, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Pre-collision system fails to provide warning or brake assist
vehicle rear-ends another vehicle without warning
system data extraction and investigation by manufacturer concludes no defect found
but driver believes system failure contributed to the accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected explosion of the sunroof can cause a loud noise, shattering of glass, and potentially lead to physical harm or injury to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Loud explosion or popping sound
sudden shattering of the sunroof glass
glass fragments falling into the vehicle
potential scratching or injury to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective rear window tinting can cause impaired visibility, which can lead to accidents or reduce the driver's ability to safely operate the vehicle.
symptoms: Bubbles and smeared adhesive on the rear window
making it difficult to view what is behind the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective panoramic sunroof can cause sudden and unexpected shattering, which can distract the driver and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Bubbles and cracks on the sunroof
with the outer edges appearing to have cracked all the way around.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective windshield can cause sudden and unexpected cracking, which can impair visibility and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Windshield cracking without visible signs of impact
cracks extending in length while driving
and rapid spread of cracks after minor impacts.
